  <!-- Privacy -->
  <section class="section privacy" id="privacy">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Privacy & Security</h2>
        <p class="lead">How we handle data as an AI-first CRM. <span class="small">Last updated: November 3, 2025</span></p>
      </div>
      <div class="policy">
        <p class="small"><strong>Note:</strong> This is a practical template and not legal advice. Review with counsel for your use case.</p>

        <h3>Roles & scope</h3>
        <p>For customer lead and contact data stored in Rithink, we act as a <em>processor</em>. For our own website visitors and marketing, we act as a <em>controller</em>.</p>

        <h3>What we process</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Contact and company details (e.g., name, email, role, firmographics)</li>
          <li>Interactions (forms, chat, email threads, bookings, summaries, notes)</li>
          <li>Operational metadata (owners, SLAs, cadence steps, timestamps)</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Purposes</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>To capture and respond to inbound leads and book meetings</li>
          <li>To operate CRM records, pipelines, tasks and messaging sequences</li>
          <li>To measure and improve response times and conversion</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Legal basis (GDPR)</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><em>Legitimate interests</em> in responding to business inquiries and operating CRM workflows</li>
          <li><em>Consent</em> where required (e.g., subscriptions, certain cookies)</li>
          <li><em>Contract</em> for customers using our product</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Security</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Encryption in transit (TLS) and at rest</li>
          <li>Role-based access controls, 2FA/SSO options</li>
          <li>Daily backups and disaster recovery procedures</li>
          <li>Regular vulnerability scans and least-privilege policies</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>AI & model usage</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Customer data is <strong>not</strong> used to train foundation models by default.</li>
          <li>Tenant-level fine-tuning or prompt libraries only with explicit opt-in.</li>
          <li>We retain operational prompts/summaries as part of your CRM records.</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Retention</h3>
        <p>CRM records persist while your account is active. You can export or delete data on request; backups roll off on a schedule.</p>

        <h3>Sub-processors & transfers</h3>
        <p>We use reputable providers for hosting, messaging and analytics. Where data leaves the EEA, we use appropriate safeguards (e.g., SCCs). A current sub-processor list is available on request.</p>

        <h3>Data subject rights</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Access, rectification, erasure, restriction, portability, objection (where applicable)</li>
          <li>Contact: <a href="mailto:rijad.alibasic@hotmail.com">rijad.alibasic@hotmail.com</a></li>
          <li>DPA: available on request</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Cookies</h3>
        <p>We use essential cookies and may use analytics with consent. You can change preferences at any time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

